<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHINESE MASSACRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In "A Letter From China" (Op-Ed Page, June 7), an official of a Chinese 
corporation near Hong Kong lamented that the Chinese government had become a 
"Fascist government" and China's People's Liberation Army had become a "Fascist 
army." He makes the same error as many Westerners unable to see the true 
totalitarian face of communism. 
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government and its "Liberation" army remain what they have always 
been, a Communist government and a Communist army and they behave like 
Communist institutions invariably behave, zealous of power and harsh on those 
who dare to challenge it. 
</P>
<P>
S. JAFFE 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
