<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAIR HOUSING AGENCY SELECTS NEW DIRECTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stephanie Knapik, assistant director of the Westside Fair Housing Council, has 
been named executive director of the nonprofit group. 
</P>
<P>
Knapik, 38, has worked at the council since 1985. She was previously center 
director of the Los Angeles Chapter of the National Organization for Women, and 
a survey analyst at RAND Corp. 
</P>
<P>
The Westside Fair Housing Council oversees the implementation of local, state 
and federal fair housing laws in West Los Angeles. 
