<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG DEAL RESTAURANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Is there someone you need to impress? You'll have to spend a little money, but 
then haute attitudes don't come cheap in this town. 
</P>
<P>
L'Ermitage, 730 N. La Cienega Blvd., Los Angeles. (213) 652-5840. Style: L.A.'s 
first serious French restaurant continues to set the standard. Setting: 
Comfortable modern elegance. Recommended dishes: Feuillete with salmon in 
beurre blanc; roasted squab; aiguillete of duck breast in red wine sauce. Cost 
per person: $40-$75. 
</P>
<P>
L'Orangerie, 903 N. La Cienega Blvd., West Hollywood. (213) 652-9770. Style: 
Costly classic French. Setting: Drop-dead gorgeous. Recommended dishes: Seafood 
salad with raspberry vinegar; rack of lamb; tarte aux pommes chaudes (apple 
tart). Cost per person: $50-$70. 
</P>
<P>
Michael's, 1147 Third Street, Santa Monica. (213) 451-0843. Style: One of 
L.A.'s most expensive restaurants and proud of it. Setting: Gorgeous outdoor 
garden, lots of contemporary art. Recommended dishes: Saddle of lamb; chicken 
breast with duck liver and morel mushrooms. Cost per person: $60-$75. 
</P>
<P>
Rex Il Ristorante, 617 S. Olive St., Los Angeles. (213) 627-2300. Style: 
Perfect pasta in precious portions. Setting: Lusciously luxurious with lots of 
Lalique. Recommended dishes: Ravioli di pesce (fish ravioli); baby salmon in 
sorrel sauce; veal with artichoke hearts. Cost per person: $50-$65. Kathie 
Jenkins 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Drawing, TED ENGELBART 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
Restaurant Review; List 
</P>
