<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-ASTRONAUT TRULY TO RETIRE FROM NAVY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former shuttle astronaut Richard Truly, associate NASA administrator, will 
retire from the Navy on July 1 with the rank of vice admiral, Defense Secretary 
Dick Cheney announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Truly, who has held the rank of rear admiral since September, 1983, has 
completed 30 years of military service. He will continue in his job at the 
National Aeronautics and Space Administration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
