Richard, with gold panning.; Photo, At right, some gear remains in the Ready 
Relief mine's mill and crusher building. ; Photo, Near Julian, a building from 
the Ready Relief and Hubbard mines, dating to the 1890s, still stands. But over 
the years vandals have taken souvenirs. ; Photo, 'There's lots of trouble all 
over these hills. They come up here with an arsenal. Sometimes they shoot two, 
three, four-hundred rounds. And if they don't take something, they tear it up.' 
-- Roy Larison ; Photo, Gustave Hudson, El Cajon man who filed a claim on land 
already claimed by two others. ; Photo, Prospector Bruce Herrington, who 
complains about "weekend Rambos with their guns." DAVE GATLEY / Los Angeles 
Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
