<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 2 TEEN-AGERS TRAPPED IN TUNNEL FOR 4 HOURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Simi Valley teen-agers were trapped for more than four hours early Saturday 
in a cave at Santa Susana Knolls near Simi Valley after one became stuck while 
crawling through a narrow passage, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Dean Feldman, 16, got stuck in a tunnel while following Sara Morris, 15. 
Because Feldman was stuck, Morris was unable to return to the cave's entrance, 
said Sgt. Will Howe of the Ventura County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
Two other teen-agers who had been crawling behind Feldman left the cave and 
summoned authorities after trying for more than an hour to help their 6-foot-2, 
160-pound friend squeeze through the passage, Howe said. Firefighters used an 
air chisel to widen the tunnel and free Feldman about 7:30 a.m., more than four 
hours after he became lodged there, Howe said. The teen-agers entered the cave 
during a hike, which began about 10:30 p.m. Friday, Howe said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
