an Oriental figurine. ; Photo, Main square in the East German medieval town of 
Meissen. JOY SCHALEBEN LEWIS; Photo, A landmark structure in Meissen is the 
16th-Century Albrechtsburg, a fortress, palace and cathedral that sits just off 
the Elbe River. ; Photo, Artist carefully details the final touches for a 
porcelain vase at the Meissen Porcelain Museum. 
</P>
