<DATE>
<P>
June 18, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Real Estate; Part 8; Page 15; Column 4; Real Estate Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
66 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMERCIAL SCENE; 
</P>
<P>
HOLLYWOOD APARTMENTS BOUGHT FOR CONVERSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Franklin Towers Joint Venture, a group including New York investors, has paid 
$22.75 million for the 190-unit Franklin West Towers apartment complex at 7250 
Franklin Ave., Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
Real Estate Dynamics, the seller, was represented by Weaver &amp; Co., Century 
City. The Zohn Corp., Beverly Hills, represented the buyer, which plans to 
convert the twin-tower, 13-story project to condominiums. 
</P>
