<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOTRE DAME, SYRACUSE MAKE DATE IN BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SYRACUSE, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A home game with Notre Dame and travel dates with Duke and Florida State are 
among the highlights of the 1989-1990 Syracuse basketball schedule. 
</P>
<P>
Syracuse, which was 30-8 last season when it was one of the final eight teams 
in the NCAA tournament, will play 17 of its 27 regular-season games at home, 
starting with Rutgers on Nov. 27. 
</P>
<P>
The Orangemen will host Notre Dame on Feb. 20 in a return-match and play 
Florida State in Orlando on Feb. 3. 
</P>
<P>
Duke and Syracuse will meet in Greensboro, N.C., on Dec. 6 as part of the 
inaugural Big East vs. Atlantic Coast Conference week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
