<HEADLINE>
<P>
WARRIORS RAISE THEIR TICKET PRICES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OAKLAND, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Golden State Warriors announced Tuesday that ticket prices for the 1989-90 
season will increase by an average of 21 percent. 
</P>
<P>
The increases will range from $1.50 for the least expensive seats to $5 for the 
highest-priced seats at the 15,025-seat Oakland Coliseum, the club said. 
</P>
<P>
Ticket prices will now range from $7.50 to $28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
