<HEADLINE>
<P>
SIMI VALLEY'S PATE STRUGGLES AT U. S. OPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Steve Pate of Simi Valley shot a three-over-par 73 Saturday and trails leader 
Tom Kite by 11 strokes after 54 holes of play in the 89th U. S. Open in 
Rochester, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
Pate's three-day total of 74-69-73 -- 216 left him tied for 11th place with 
eight other players, including Hal Sutton, Pate's partner for today's final 
round over the 6,902-yard East course at Oak Hill Country Club. 
</P>
</TEXT>
