<HEADLINE>
<P>
AMERICAN LEGION BASEBALL; 
</P>
<P>
BROWN THROWS 4-HITTER FOR WOODLAND HILLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By REGINA ANDERSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite missing six players because of all-star game commitments, Woodland 
Hills East defeated Newhall-Saugus, 6-1, in an inter-division District 20 
American Legion baseball game Saturday afternoon at Taft High. 
</P>
<P>
Pitcher Chris Brown improved his record to 3-0 in a complete-game four-hitter. 
He struck out eight, walked one and was helped by standout defense -- Woodland 
Hills East made no errors. 
</P>
<P>
"We stress defense and all our players are capable of rising to the occasions. 
And Chris Brown pitched a magnificent game," said Matt Borzello, Woodland Hills 
East coach. 
</P>
<P>
Second baseman Michael Kimelman had two hits and three runs batted in for 
Woodland Hills East. REGINA ANDERSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
